# ProjectFlo — Commands & Terminal Discipline

- Prefer repo tools (read/search/editor diagnostics) over terminal for reading/searching/type errors.
- Do not start dev servers as an agent; instruct the user to run `pnpm dev` if needed.
- Terminal is a scarce resource: keep terminal usage minimal and combine commands where possible.
- DB workflow (root scripts): `pnpm db:generate`, `pnpm db:push`, `pnpm db:migrate`, `pnpm db:seed`, `pnpm db:reset`, `pnpm db:studio`.
- Named migrations: run from `packages/backend` with `npx prisma migrate dev --name "kebab-case"`.
- Git safety: avoid destructive operations (no force-push without explicit confirmation).
- If node processes spiral, `taskkill /F /IM node.exe` stops all node processes (will also stop dev servers).

